{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-topic-topic-tsx","path":"/topics/pre-conception-advice-management/","result":{"data":{"firstChapter":{"id":"b4e662d9-e04d-5220-9289-f9d2f83a655d","slug":"summary","fullItemName":"Summary","subChapters":[],"depth":1,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 74faba4b-2ed9-4e92-b107-0543d10f62e4 --><h1>Pre-conception - advice and management: Summary</h1><!-- end field 74faba4b-2ed9-4e92-b107-0543d10f62e4 -->","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 61d2191c-e2a3-4e4b-999a-aa1693a16bdf --><!-- begin field ff7ff29f-c107-4125-bae2-4b448aa9cd3a --><ul><li>The goal of pre-conception care is to improve the long and short-term health outcomes of women and their children.</li><li>Pre-conception care is important because:<ul><li>Womens' health around conception and in early pregnancy impacts on their lifelong health and that of their children. </li><li>It allows physical and mental health conditions and social needs to be addressed and managed prior to pregnancy.<strong> </strong></li><li>It allows women to be aware of potential risks and make an informed decision about their pregnancy. </li><li>Many potentially modifiable risk factors which influence pregnancy outcomes are present prior to conception. This means that prenatal care is often given too late to change the outcome of the pregnancy.<strong> </strong></li></ul></li><li>Women should be offered general pre-conception advice on subjects including diet; weight management; smoking and alcohol consumption; illicit drug use; prescription, over-the-counter and herbal medicines; cervical screening; and immunization status.</li><li>If the woman has a mental health problem or chronic medical condition, specific pre-conception management advice including specialist referral should be offered where appropriate.</li><li>A history should be taken to find out whether a woman or her partner are at increased risk of having a baby with an inherited genetic disorder, and screening and counselling should be offered where appropriate.</li></ul><!-- end field ff7ff29f-c107-4125-bae2-4b448aa9cd3a --><!-- end item 61d2191c-e2a3-4e4b-999a-aa1693a16bdf -->","topic":{"id":"7fbac536-1f76-5678-a8d3-791cde12bdcc","topicId":"362122fc-a8d4-48c6-bbe1-260b84fdc035","topicName":"Pre-conception - advice and management","slug":"pre-conception-advice-management","aliases":[],"chapters":[{"id":"b4e662d9-e04d-5220-9289-f9d2f83a655d","slug":"summary","fullItemName":"Summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d516f1b7-0d03-56d1-a1ff-98ee4586d10c","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","subChapters":[]},{"id":"05f2e291-0cb3-508a-a53a-203bf7452154","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","subChapters":[{"id":"eea0164e-7605-53f2-82b1-30649c6b462b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"3107f6a6-010e-5793-b49e-f188321b5d25","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"ccdc8c20-befb-5b1b-9e44-e7d66512c304","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","subChapters":[{"id":"d2c77d6a-aa8b-5f5a-bc22-e802a1ed63dd","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"354ac657-195c-55c7-86dc-32bd495719e6","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"90c0a8b7-d685-5b54-ab19-50262a840059","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"8991e1d6-fe99-54e2-a7f0-8c087cbc913e","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"ce6a54cd-7770-5f7d-b3d4-72d82e13e288","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"cea8adf5-cc1a-59e9-b1bc-a7fe7dd9612e","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"8ebfaff6-f12e-5e6d-a4da-824f9755cc22","slug":"background-information","fullItemName":"Background information","subChapters":[{"id":"eb257b56-0f26-5b88-b016-779a5c57372a","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"}]},{"id":"cb07c890-793e-585a-b8